    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-05-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-05-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="245"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d245">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Hunter</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Adams</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1426.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-05-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 29, 1865</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatch of the 11th instant, No. 954,
                    transmitting an additional number of addresses and resolutions, occasioned by
                    the late deplorable calamity, together with an appended list of these papers,
                    has been received.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>W. HUNTER, <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic"
                            >&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                    <p>[For enclosures see Appendix, separate volume.]</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
